-- FACTBOX: S&P 500 posts third-worst year ever in 2008
-- 
-- Wed Dec 31, 2008 4:38pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/12/31/us-usa-stocks-sp500-ranking-factbox-idUSTRE4BU4MQ20081231

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The S&P 500  .SPX  ended 2008 down 38.5 percent, marking its third-worst year ever. 

 Below is a list of the 10 worst years for the index by percentage declines. Year Pct Change 1931 -47.07 1937 -38.59 2008 -38.49 1974 -29.72 1930 -24.48 2002 -23.37 1941 -17.86 1973 -17.43 1940 -15.29 1932 -15.13 Source: Standard and Poor's (Reporting by  Rodrigo Campos ; Editing by  Jonathan Oatis )